[src:tree-sitter-parsing/compiler-compiler] The program rule is a *test* function that calls declaration, a *test* rule, that returns *success* or *failure*.
[src:tree-sitter-parsing/compiler-compiler] The $ loop operator repeatedly calling declaration until *failure* is returned.
[src:tree-sitter-parsing/compiler-compiler] The $ operator is always successful, even when there are zero declaration.
[src:tree-sitter-parsing/compiler-compiler] Above program would always return success.
