[src:tree-sitter-parsing/compiler-compiler] The character sets of these early compilers were limited.
[src:tree-sitter-parsing/compiler-compiler] The character **/** was used for the alternant (or) operator.
[src:tree-sitter-parsing/compiler-compiler] Describes a construct of A followed by B or C.
[src:tree-sitter-parsing/compiler-compiler] A sequence X Y has an implied X **and** Y meaning.
[src:tree-sitter-parsing/compiler-compiler] The order of evaluation is always left to right as an input character sequence is being specified by the ordering of the tests.
